(CNN)Ray Liotta's daughter, Karsen, 23, posted a tribute to her dad on Instagram. "Those who knew him, loved him," she wrote alongside a photo of the pair. "You are the best Dad anyone could ask for. I love you. Thank you for everything." She added a heart emoji. On May 26, Liotta died in his sleep at age 67 while in the Dominican Republic filming his latest project, "Dangerous Waters." He shared Karsen with his ex-wife, Michelle Grace. He is survived by his fianc√©e Jacy Nittolo. Liotta supported his daughter's acting ambitions during an "Absolute Radio" interview in 2016. "I am a true believer that if this is what she wants to do, what am I gonna do?" he said. "It's what you do and how you handle that time in between, which is what messes up a lot of actors." 